1. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper investigates the performance of wireless systems using channel coding and transmission rates. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper considers queueing constraints in wireless systems. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with the performance of wireless systems under statistical queuing constraints. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper considers the performance of wireless systems under block fading, which is relevant to multimedia transmission. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may consider the security implications of channel coding in wireless systems.
